sentences: Robert Keith Young (born 16 May 1945) is an English musician and author, who became famous for being the unofficial fifth member of the rock band Status Quo.
Based on this experience he was hired by the management of Status Quo, after they had their first hit with "Pictures of Matchstick Men" in 1968.
As early as 1969 he started writing songs for the band.
In the following years he wrote a number of songs for Status Quo, usually together with lead guitarist and singer Francis Rossi.
In 1978 the book "Alias The Compass" was released which contained poems and song lyrics by Bob Young, written while he was working with Status Quo.

Together with guitarist Micky Moody, whom he got to know when Moody supported Status Quo with his band SNAFU, Young founded "Young & Moody" (also known as The Young & Moody Band) in 1976.
Moody joined David Coverdale's band Whitesnake in 1978, but continued to record with Young.
In 1986 Bob Young's first solo album In Quo Country was released.
